🔹 1️⃣ “Task ka core logic run” ka matlab:-
Task ka core logic matlab: jo kaam task ke liye specifically design kiya gaya hai, wo sab executor ke execute() method me perform hota hai.
Example ka scope:-
Task Type	                          Core Logic Example
Provisioning:--------------Identity ko role assign karna, entitlement add/remove
Compliance:----------------Check karna ki user ke paas valid access hai ya nahi
Notifications:-------------Email ya system alert send karna
Workflow Integration:------Approval workflow trigger karna
Custom Calculation:--------Data process karke TaskResult me store karna.

🔹 2️⃣ public Map<String, Object> getResults():-
Purpose:-
Ye method task execution ke results return karta hai,
Engine ya workflow usko read karke next step decide kar sakta hai.

🔹 3️⃣ public void init(Task task):-
Purpose:-
Task execution ke shuru me initialization ke liye,
Developer task-specific setup ya log messages yaha kar sakta hai.

🔹 4️⃣ public void finish(TaskResult result):-
Purpose:-
Task complete hone ke baad cleanup aur final updates ke liye,
TaskResult ka final status, messages, or auditing yaha set karte hain.

🔹 5️⃣ public void setParameters(Map<String, Object> params):-
Purpose:-
Task me custom input parameters set karne ke liye,
Executor ke andar ye parameters read karke logic me use hote hain.

🔹 6️⃣ public Map<String, Object> getParameters():-
Purpose:-
Task execution ke beech me parameters read karne ke liye,
Logic decide karne me ya workflow me ye kaam aata hai.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ public void execute(TaskContext context):-
Purpose:
Ye main method hai jo task engine ke through call hota hai,
TaskContext me Task instance, TaskResult, parameters sab available hote hain.
Isme task ka core logic run hota hai.

Example:-
import sailpoint.task.TaskContext;
import sailpoint.task.TaskResult;

public class CustomExecutor {

    public void execute(TaskContext context) {
        TaskResult result = context.getTaskResult();
        System.out.println("Executing task: " + context.getTask().getName());

        // Simple logic
        result.setStatus(TaskResult.Status.Running);
        result.addMessage("Task is running...");

        // Complete task
        result.setCompletionStatus(TaskResult.Status.Completed);
        result.addMessage("Task completed successfully.");
    }
}
Sample Output:-
Executing task: DemoTask
TaskResult Status: Running
TaskResult Message: Task is running...
TaskResult Completion Status: Completed
TaskResult Message: Task completed successfully.
