🔹 1️⃣ public void process():-
Purpose:-
Ye main entry point hai aggregation workflow ka.
Iska kaam hai:-
System me registered sab identities (users) ke liye aggregation run karna.
Har identity ke sab linked accounts aggregate karna.
Har account ke attributes process karna.
Developer yaha core aggregation logic implement karta hai.

Sample Conceptual Output:-
Starting aggregation process...
Aggregating identity: jokerboy
Aggregating identity: alice

🔹 2️⃣ public void aggregateIdentity(Identity identity):-
Purpose:-
Ye single identity ka aggregation karta hai.
Kaam:-
Identity ka naam log karna.
Identity se linked sab accounts pe aggregateAccount() call karna.

Sample Output:-
Aggregating identity: jokerboy
Aggregating identity: alice

🔹 3️⃣ public void aggregateAccount(Account account):-
Purpose:-
Ye method account-level aggregation karta hai.
Kaam:-
Account ka naam log karna.
Account ke attributes ko processAttributes() me bhejna.
Aggregated account data ko store karna (map/dictionary me).
Sample Output:-
Aggregating account: JiraAccount
Aggregating account: EmailAccount

🔹 4️⃣ public void processAttributes(Map<String,Object> attrs):-
Purpose:-
Ye attribute-level processing karta hai.
Ye method account ya identity attributes ko process/update karta hai.
Kaam:-
Missing attributes fill karna (example: email not found → default value)
Business rules apply karna (role validation, normalization)
Attribute transformations (uppercase username, masking data, etc.)

Example:-
Processing attributes: {username=jokerboy, role=User}
Processing attributes: {username=alice, role=Admin, email=alice@example.com}

🔹 🔹 Real Project Simulation (Notepad-Friendly Code)
import java.util.*;

// Account class
class Account {
    private String accountName;
    private Map<String,Object> attributes = new HashMap<>();

    public Account(String accountName){ this.accountName = accountName; }
    public String getAccountName(){ return accountName; }
    public Map<String,Object> getAttributes(){ return attributes; }
    public void addAttribute(String key, Object value){ attributes.put(key,value); }
}

// Identity class
class Identity {
    private String username;
    private List<Account> accounts = new ArrayList<>();

    public Identity(String username){ this.username = username; }
    public String getUsername(){ return username; }
    public List<Account> getAccounts(){ return accounts; }
    public void addAccount(Account account){ accounts.add(account); }
}

// Aggregation Executor
public class AggregationExecutor {

    private Map<String, Map<String,Object>> accountData = new HashMap<>();
    private List<Identity> identities = new ArrayList<>();

    public void addIdentity(Identity identity){ identities.add(identity); }

    public void process(){
        System.out.println("Starting aggregation process...");
        for(Identity id : identities){
            aggregateIdentity(id);
        }
    }

    public void aggregateIdentity(Identity identity){
        System.out.println("Aggregating identity: " + identity.getUsername());
        for(Account acc : identity.getAccounts()){
            aggregateAccount(acc);
        }
    }

    public void aggregateAccount(Account account){
        System.out.println("Aggregating account: " + account.getAccountName());
        processAttributes(account.getAttributes());
        accountData.put(account.getAccountName(), account.getAttributes());
    }

    public void processAttributes(Map<String,Object> attrs){
        System.out.println("Processing attributes: " + attrs);
        if(!attrs.containsKey("email")){
            attrs.put("email","notfound@example.com");
        }
    }

    public Map<String, Map<String,Object>> getAccountData(){ return accountData; }

    public static void main(String[] args){
        AggregationExecutor executor = new AggregationExecutor();

        // Accounts
        Account acc1 = new Account("JiraAccount");
        acc1.addAttribute("username","jokerboy");
        acc1.addAttribute("role","User");

        Account acc2 = new Account("EmailAccount");
        acc2.addAttribute("username","alice");
        acc2.addAttribute("role","Admin");
        acc2.addAttribute("email","alice@example.com");

        // Identities
        Identity id1 = new Identity("jokerboy");
        id1.addAccount(acc1);

        Identity id2 = new Identity("alice");
        id2.addAccount(acc2);

        executor.addIdentity(id1);
        executor.addIdentity(id2);

        // Run aggregation
        executor.process();

        System.out.println("\n--- Aggregated Account Data ---");
        System.out.println(executor.getAccountData());
    }
}
🔹 🔹 Sample Output:-
Starting aggregation process...
Aggregating identity: jokerboy
Aggregating account: JiraAccount
Processing attributes: {username=jokerboy, role=User}
Aggregating identity: alice
Aggregating account: EmailAccount
Processing attributes: {username=alice, role=Admin, email=alice@example.com}

--- Aggregated Account Data ---
{JiraAccount={username=jokerboy, role=User, email=notfound@example.com},
 EmailAccount={username=alice, role=Admin, email=alice@example.com}}
