🔹 🔥 Reconciliation kya hota hai?
👉 Reconciliation = Compare + Sync
System Data (Accounts)  VS  IdentityIQ Data (Identity)

✔ Check karta hai:-
Kya user ke paas extra access hai?
Kya missing access hai?
Kya mismatch hai?
👉 Phir system ko sync/update karta hai.

🔹 1️⃣ public void reconcile():-
✅ Purpose:-
Ye main reconciliation process start karta hai.
Kaam:-
System vs Identity compare karna
Differences identify karna
Result list me store karna

🔹 Example:-
public void reconcile(){
    System.out.println("Starting reconciliation...");

    List<Object> results = new ArrayList<>();

    // Example comparison logic
    for(String user : systemData.keySet()){
        if(!identityData.containsKey(user)){
            results.add("Missing Identity for: " + user);
        } else if(!systemData.get(user).equals(identityData.get(user))){
            results.add("Mismatch for: " + user);
        } else {
            results.add("Match: " + user);
        }
    }

    setReconciliationResults(results);
}

🔹 2️⃣ public void setReconciliationResults(List<Object> list)
✅ Purpose:-
Reconciliation ke final results store karta hai
Ye results baad me:-
UI me dikhte hain
Reports me jaate hain
Next workflow me use hote hain

🔹 Example:-
private List<Object> reconciliationResults;

public void setReconciliationResults(List<Object> list){
    this.reconciliationResults = list;
    System.out.println("Results stored...");
}

🔹 3️⃣ public List<Object> getReconciliationResults()
✅ Purpose:-
Stored reconciliation results ko retrieve karta hai

Reporting, logging, auditing me use hota hai

🔹 Example:-
public List<Object> getReconciliationResults(){
    return reconciliationResults;
}

🔹 🔥 Full Notepad-Friendly Code
import java.util.*;

public class ReconciliationExecutor {

    private Map<String,String> systemData = new HashMap<>();
    private Map<String,String> identityData = new HashMap<>();
    private List<Object> reconciliationResults;

    // Constructor - sample data
    public ReconciliationExecutor(){
        // System data (actual accounts)
        systemData.put("jokerboy","Admin");
        systemData.put("alice","User");
        systemData.put("bob","Manager");

        // IdentityIQ data
        identityData.put("jokerboy","Admin");
        identityData.put("alice","Admin"); // mismatch
    }

    // 1️⃣ Reconcile
    public void reconcile(){
        System.out.println("Starting reconciliation...\n");

        List<Object> results = new ArrayList<>();

        for(String user : systemData.keySet()){
            if(!identityData.containsKey(user)){
                results.add("Missing Identity: " + user);
            }
            else if(!systemData.get(user).equals(identityData.get(user))){
                results.add("Mismatch: " + user);
            }
            else{
                results.add("Match: " + user);
            }
        }

        setReconciliationResults(results);
    }

    // 2️⃣ Store results
    public void setReconciliationResults(List<Object> list){
        this.reconciliationResults = list;
        System.out.println("Reconciliation results stored.\n");
    }

    // 3️⃣ Get results
    public List<Object> getReconciliationResults(){
        return reconciliationResults;
    }

    // Main method
    public static void main(String[] args){
        ReconciliationExecutor executor = new ReconciliationExecutor();

        executor.reconcile();

        System.out.println("--- Reconciliation Results ---");
        for(Object obj : executor.getReconciliationResults()){
            System.out.println(obj);
        }
    }
}
🔹 🔥 Output
Starting reconciliation...

Reconciliation results stored.

--- Reconciliation Results ---
Match: jokerboy
Mismatch: alice
Missing Identity: bob
